<h2 class=\"showTitle\"><em>Kidding</em></h2>
<p>New photographs by Daniel Terna</p>
<p>On view: June 1 – July 12<br/>
<br/>
			Opening Reception: June 1, 5-7:30pm</p>
<p>For information, please contact:<br/>
			The Wild Project 212.228.1195 • <a href=\"mailto:info@thewildproject.com\" target=\"_blank\">info@thewildproject.com</a></p>
<p>The Wild Project presents Kidding, a solo exhibition featuring new work by Daniel Terna. Transforming everyday snapshots into the drama of the quotidian, Terna’s photographs—shot in New York, Los Angeles, and Switzerland—capture the showmanship in our daily lives. With an unfixed narrative, Terna homes in on ambiguous scenery and the pose, drawing out the artifice in seemingly natural situations. Moving fluidly across photographic genres, the artist combines staged studio work with personal documentary photographs, a mechanism that acts as another form of visual deception. - Kkory Trolio</p>

<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost:3000/wp-content/themes/wildproject/images/gallery/2014-Kidding.jpg\"/></p>
